{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ae6e71aa-82dc-4804-b545-69c24dc4e13d","content":"No pipeline files found in the repo, so here's general guidance for the migration:\n\n### Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script)\n\n**Before (VSTest):**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblies: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform):**\n```yaml\n# 1. Run tests with dotnet test — MTP is used automatically\n#    when your test projects reference Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n\n# 2. Publish TRX results (unchanged)\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n# 3. Publish code coverage\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n| Concern | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| **Test runner** | Remove `VSTest@3`; use `dotnet test` (via `DotNetCoreCLI@2` or a `script` step) |\n| **TRX reports** | Pass `--logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"` — same format, works with `PublishTestResults@2` |\n| **Code coverage** | Use `--collect \"Code Coverage\"`. For Cobertura XML output (needed by `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`), add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package or use `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"` with the Microsoft collector |\n| **Test filtering** | Replace `testFilterCriteria` with `--filter \"Category=Unit\"` on the `arguments` line |\n\n### In your `.csproj` files\n\nMake sure each test project uses the MTP runner:\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSTest\" Version=\"...\" />\n```\n\nThis replaces the old `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` combo. After the package update, `dotnet test` automatically uses MTP.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cd4808a6-2378-449c-a78e-065103629fe1","outputTokens":696,"requestId":"BD07:4FC4C:1D3DA5E:20E2736:6A07C4C8"},"id":"4022738c-9291-4981-86c1-98c780893750","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:13:57.979Z","parentId":"e5d09cf2-fd28-429f-99b5-49fa7ae680af"}
